171. Flaminia: see note on l. 61. Roads leading from Rome were lined with tombs, for Roman law from the earliest period sorbade burial within the city, cf. 8,146. Latina: this road led from Rome by the porta Capena, diverged to the left from the via Appia, passed through the hilly district of Tusculum (hence 5, 55 clivosae. . .Latinae), and touched Ferentinum, Frusino, and Juvenal’s native town Aquinum, finally rejoin- ing the Appia at Casilinum in Campania.
